<br>
Reading this new thread got me thinking about it though.  I've been a caster - well, a cleric in the higher levels.  Granted this was long ago, but anyway.<br>
<br>
Casters are all about control.  Ghetto root mezzing is a skill you don't see a lot of people possessing these days.  I have brought control to some pretty gruesome pulls in my day by myself....and the typical group will probably have at least 2 rooters, or others that can provide some support.<br>
<br>
If you are too low on mana to be of use in a flop pull then it's still your fault, unless the puller wasn't listening to you and pulling too fast.  You should stay around 80-90 mana in an exp group.  You're not supposed to pull crazy till casters are oom then med.<br>
<br>
I understand that there are exceptions to this of course.  But not enough to warrant a discussion about it.  Chances are if this is happening frequently, then it is a result of the lack player skill.<br>
<br>
Look at it this way.  If melee had the ability to gate, and they stood looking around for half the fight before clicking attack, do you think THEY have the right to gate?<br>
<br>
Seems a lot of people need to take a trip back lower guk, or hell even karnors and learn to play their class.  Kids grow up too fast these days.  Rawr<br>
<br>
