<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
I was in the Hole the other day we get a nasty over pull, partly due to the set up of The Hole and how the mobs becomes adds quickly. Group was varied in levels, so I was keeping in mind what my group could handle. Our cleric and enchanter were both lower than everyone, out enchanter being the lowest. Poor guy died two or three times but took it like a champ. We snagged him 90% res both times for a cleric that was near by. None of our casters bailed. I suppose we are lucky. <br>
<br>
But, we did run into a nasty problem. I was trying to FD split a few elementals and our rogue followed me in, just to watch. I already knew that the elementals saw invis but I didnt expect for the rogue, since I told the group, to follow close. So, I darkness one, wait..wait..wait and FD right before they hit me. EVERY time I did this our rogue was behind me and got aggro and he hauled arse back to the group and almost got our casters dead. Our second rogue did this as well.<br>
<br>
As far as spell slots go, I'd kill for two more. I have so many AC/ATK taps that I dont use because my slots are full.<br>
<br>
1. Life Tap<br>
2. Darkness<br>
3. Boil blood<br>
4. Heart Flutter<br>
5. Spear of disease<br>
6. Grim aura<br>
7. Scream of Death<br>
8. FD<br>
<br>
Now, I can take my self buffs out but they dont last long enough to warrent sitting down and rememing em. I'd use them because they make a diffrence. Maybe I should just drop my self buffs once I cast em..<br>
