<br>
When I pull, most of the time I can see if there is going to be a problem before I bring the mob(s) to the party...<br>
<br>
Normally my Lineup of spells contained...<br>
<br>
1.) Touch of Votalis (Self Life Tap)<br>
2.) Zevfeers Bite (Team heal/Life Tap)<br>
3.) Torrent of Hate     <br>
4.) Torrent of Fatigue<br>
5.) Torrent of Pain   (All 3 mob debuff, group buff)<br>
6.) Terror of Death (Aggro spell)<br>
7.) Deathly Temptation (SK Gimp Lich) (Swapped out with buffs as needed such as Mental Corruption, Cloak of the Akheva, etc )<br>
8.) Death Peace<br>
<br>
Being I can summon corpses up to level 65, death isn't really an issue to me, part of the risk... though unnecessary death can be avoided if you know when to hold em and when to fold em as they say...  Espically in any PoP zones, where summoning isn't really an issue, but coffins are a small price to pay... stand in the gap when things get fun, its the rush that is the most fun part about it all...<br>
<br>
But yes, Gating is situational... but the puller will be best to tell when or when not to pull out, because they can normally see just how bad things are going to be when they are pulling mobs.<br>
