<br>
For a necro, she's pretty good at crowd control, so long as there are no more than two or three adds. Sometimes a necro style mez or root just isn't enough (both are very short duration).<br>
<br>
If the going looks bad and there's no way it's not going to be a total wipe, I can evac, lose aggro and still be in-zone ready to summon corpses, rez the cleric etc. Is this cowardly? I don't think so, it's a sensible use of your (pixelated) human resources.<br>
<br>
I agree with the original poster. If a caster is gating out at the first sign of trouble, dump 'em and look for a replacement. But for melee classes to expect a caster to die in an obviously hopeless situation is just selfish.<br>
<br>
